{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017o5qrt3MWDSxnqvNV28J6V","type":"tool_result","content":"  - `chatgpt.test.ts` (20 tests): mapping tree traversal with BFS ordering, circular reference protection via visited set, flat message format fallback, object/string content extraction, system/tool role handling, empty content skipping, default title assignment, timestamp conversion\n  - `claude.test.ts` (22 tests): text/string/array content extraction, content field priority (text > content), role mapping (human→user, assistant passthrough, missing→user), non-text content part filtering, edge cases (empty messages, no sender, multiple conversations)\n  - `gemini.test.ts` (24 tests): all 3 format variations (Takeout flat array, AI Studio conversation array, single conversation object), multi-part message joining, content fallback field, role mapping (model→assistant), createTime propagation, empty parts skipping\n  - `processor.test.ts` (10 tests): detectProvider auto-detection across all formats, priority ordering (chatgpt before gemini for ambiguous title+messages), invalid/empty input handling\n- 129 total tests (was 53), all passing, build verified\n- Deployed to staging — app running (308 redirect to auth)\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **runeval**: 129 tests now. Remaining untested: crypto.ts, auth/tokens.ts, auth/refresh.ts, email.ts, logger.ts, openai.ts, garmin/adapter.ts (all require mocking external deps)\n- **All repos**: Clean audit (except known unfixable transitive deps), tests passing, CI active, branches clean\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-20 — Run 40\n\n### What was done\n\n**groceryGenius — WCAG accessibility attributes for interactive components (PR #57, auto-merged)**\n- Added `aria-label` to 4 Radix UI sliders in `location-preferences.tsx` with dynamic current-value text (store radius, price/time/distance weights)\n- Added `role=\"button\"`, `tabIndex={0}`, and `aria-label` to drag handle in `shopping-list.tsx` so screen readers announce \"Drag to reorder {item}\"\n- Added `aria-label` to icon-only remove buttons (X) and add button (Plus) in `shopping-list.tsx`\n- Added `aria-label` to delete photo button and per-item remove buttons in `receipt-upload.tsx`\n- Connected store select and date input to their labels via `htmlFor`/`id` in `receipt-upload.tsx`\n- Added contextual `aria-label` to favorite store heart toggle buttons (\"Add X to favorites\" / \"Remove X from favorites\") in `favorite-stores.tsx`\n- 4 files changed, 81 tests passing, build clean\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **groceryGenius**: Accessibility now solid for interactive controls. Remaining opportunities: component-level React tests (would need jsdom), integration tests for API routes\n- **promptlibrary**: Similar accessibility gaps (StarRating missing aria, tab semantics) — good candidate for next a11y pass\n- **All repos**: Clean audit (except known unfixable transitive deps), tests passing, CI active, branches clean\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-20 — Run 41\n\n### What was done\n\n**promptlibrary — WCAG accessibility attributes across all interactive components (PR #20, auto-merged)**\n- Refactored `StarRating` component: `role=\"radiogroup\"` with `aria-checked` radio buttons, arrow key keyboard navigation between stars, `focus-visible` ring styling\n- Added tab semantics to `PromptDetail` tabs: `role=\"tablist\"`, `role=\"tab\"`, `aria-selected`, `aria-controls`, `id`-linked `tabpanel` elements\n- Added tab semantics to `MyPrompts` filter tabs: `role=\"tablist\"`, `role=\"tab\"`, `aria-selected`\n- Converted visibility toggle in submit page to `role=\"switch\"` with `aria-checked` and `aria-label`\n- Connected all form labels to inputs via `htmlFor`/`id` across submit page (5 fields), output form (2 fields), rating form (1 field), settings page (1 field + sr-only label)\n- Replaced empty `alt=\"\"` on all avatar images with descriptive alt text (\"username's avatar\") in Nav, PromptCard, and PromptDetail (5 instances)\n- Added `role=\"alert\"` to all error message containers for screen reader live announcements (4 instances across submit, my-prompts, output form, rating form, settings)\n- Added contextual `aria-label` to revoke buttons in settings (\"Revoke API key {name}\")\n- 7 files changed, 66 tests passing, build clean\n- Deployed to staging — app running (302 redirect to auth)\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **promptlibrary**: Accessibility now solid for all interactive controls. Remaining opportunities: component-level React tests (would need jsdom), skip-to-content link, heading hierarchy audit\n- **scripts**: Has MutationObserver memory leak in Callisto Auto Control Setup, hardcoded LDAP names in Callisto PageKey, code duplication between userscript and extension — but these are personal automation scripts, low priority\n- **All repos**: Clean audit (except known unfixable transitive deps), tests passing, CI active, branches clean\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-20 — Run 42\n\n### What was done\n\n**promptlibrary — ESLint configuration with TypeScript and Next.js rules (PR #22, auto-merged)**\n- Added standalone ESLint flat config (`eslint.config.mjs`) with:\n  - TypeScript support via `typescript-eslint`\n  - React hooks plugin (`eslint-plugin-react-hooks`)\n  - Next.js plugin (`@next/eslint-plugin-next`)\n  - Node.js globals for server-side files (lib/, api/, middleware)\n  - Extension directory excluded (browser JS with chrome/document globals)\n- Fixed 2 lint errors surfaced by the new config:\n  - `src/app/my-prompts/page.tsx`: `<a>` tag → `<Link>` from `next/link` (no-html-link-for-pages)\n  - `src/lib/sanitize.ts`: removed unnecessary regex escape `\\/` → `/` in bearer token pattern\n- Added `npm run lint` script to package.json\n- Added lint step to CI workflow (runs before type check)\n- Result: 0 errors, 5 warnings (all expected no-img-element for external OAuth avatar URLs)\n- 66 tests passing, build clean\n- Deployed to 